This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on December 21, 2012. The memorandum addresses federal employee pay schedules and rates that are set by administrative discretion. It states that any increases or general raises in pay should be suspended for executive branch employees from January 1, 2011, to December 31, 2012. The memorandum also instructs executive departments and agencies to continue adhering to this policy until March 27, 2013, after which statutory pay adjustments may be made. The memorandum emphasizes that it is not intended to create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or its entities. The Director of the Office of Personnel Management is authorized to issue guidance on implementing the memorandum and publish it in the Federal Register.